title: For Sale/Trade:  FNH Pistole Modell 27 *** TRADE PENDING ***
postcontent: CZ Kal 7.62 (.32 acp) Nazi WWII pistol made in Czechoslovakia shortly before or during WWII when the FNH plant was under German administration.  It has the Nazi eagle on Swastika mark on the barrel and on the slide and the Waffen eagle on the frame (WaA7R).  It's fully functional and in great shape.      German officers and police used this pistol extensively, and it was brought to this country in large numbers by returning soldiers.  Many model 27 pistols, like this one, are marked with a German World War II code (fnh) to denote place of manufacture.  These are usually inferior in workmanship and finish to those without the code marking, but are serviceable pistols and more collectable.    This pistol would make a great addition to your WWII or CZ collection or a great pocket gun for Self Protection.
